# ADGM PPT — Brand Book 2025 (mandatory)

When creating, editing, or exporting **any** ADGM presentation (in-app, PPT Master, HTML deck, or Cursor-generated slides), always follow the shared brand guidelines.

## Read first

1. `docs/brand-2025/PPT-BRAND-RULES.md`
2. `src/config/adgmBrandForDeck.ts` (export tokens)
3. `src/config/brand.ts` (full Brand Book 2025)
4. `tools/adgm-deck-craft/MASTER.md` (craft + brand combined)

## Non-negotiable brand rules

- **Tagline:** Path to Forward (title or closing slide)
- **Short name:** ADGM on slides (not full legal name in marketing style)
- **Primary colours:** Clearsky `#0087FF`, Slate `#A3ADC2`, Cyan `#AFFAFF`
- **Navy:** `#00092A` (headers, title hero), mid `#001C7D`, deep `#002ED1`
- **Secondary:** Royal `#002ED1`, Mint `#E5F0F0`, Sand `#F0E8D8`
- **Typography:** Gilroy display, Aptos body, Madani Arabic for Arabic
- **Layout:** 16:9, white canvas; Clearsky for accents only (full navy allowed on title hero)
- **Footer:** `ADGM · Path to Forward · Confidential` + slide number
- **Do not use:** off-brand purples, generic template blues, non-ADGM gradients

## Code integration

- AI prompts: `server/adgmBrandGuidelines.mjs` + `server/presentationBuilderPrompts.mjs`
- PPTX export: `src/utils/presentationPptxExport.ts` + `mckinseyDeckDesign.ts`
- HTML export: `src/utils/presentationHtmlDeckExport.ts`
- Always merge `brandCheck` via `mergeBrandCheck()` / `applyBrandToDeck()`

## With craft skills

Apply brand **first**, then McKinsey + Open Design + Claude Design + PPT Master per `UNIFIED_PPT_CURSOR_PROMPT`.
